body:
So I&#039;ve been pretty hyped for the Swain update, he&#039;s always been a character I thought had a lot of potential and Riot really pulled it off in my opinion. A couple days after the reveal a Rioter said that Swain had tricked the demon into a Faustian bargain, only reversed and basically had control over the demon and its powers. Unfortunately this event wasn&#039;t really explained in Swain&#039;s lore, which sadly means it will basically never be explained in any great detail in a story. For those of you who haven&#039;t read the Swain bio yet, I&#039;ll give you this short little passage about how Swain captured the demon:

&quot;Though his meticulous preparations took many years, Swain and his remaining allies seized control of Noxus in a single night. Physically restored by the demon, he crushed Darkwill in full view of his followers, leaving the throne shattered and empty.&quot;

It&#039;s not even horrible storytelling, it&#039;s just so vague and leaves so much to be desired. Don&#039;t get me wrong, Swain is the main character and any character whose power stems from something else SHOULD be the main focus of their own story, but I feel like even a couple sentences to a paragraph could have made the Demon&#039;s little piece of the story infinitely better. It doesn&#039;t have to be the most in depth thing ever, but you also can&#039;t deny that having Swain see a &quot;darkness&quot; after every battle and realizing the ravens are eating secrets only to then explain what he did about this fact in two sentences that don&#039;t even explain what the demon is, how it was tricked into the bargain, what powers this even gives Swain, etc. just feels super unsatisfying. That passage basically just reads like &quot;Swain noticed the demon and then he captured the demon and then something something cool he&#039;s superpowered now and he has the throne and the end.&quot;

Again, Riot hit it out of the park with the Swain update and basically everything in the Noxian lore update besides this little rant about the Demon was amazing. I love Darius, I can&#039;t wait to learn more about LeBlanc, the Faceless is super cool (and is probably LeBlanc), and I love the fact that Noxus isn&#039;t just a bunch of evil dudes who literally live inside a skull mountain anymore. There&#039;s a lot of depth and room to explore for future stories, and that&#039;s an awesome thing. I&#039;m a little sad we didn&#039;t get Riven and more backstory for Sion, but hopefully we&#039;ll see Riven in Ionia when Irelia or Akali reworks come out.

That being said, I can&#039;t shake the feeling that Riot needs to give a little more explanation for side characters who are integral to champion kits. I had the same problem when Kayn came out, Rhaast is literally half of Kayn&#039;s kit but we know basically nothing about him other than that he&#039;s particularly bloodthirsty and one of the five darkin. I do believe he is the Well of Death mentioned in LeBlanc&#039;s lore and hopefully we get more story for him when Aatrox or a new darkin comes out, but at the same time it seems like the best time to go in-depth on a side character&#039;s story is when the main character of said story releases. Elise and the Spider God is another painfully vague example that comes to mind.

Anyways, that&#039;s just a small rant from a lore nerd. I only rant about small stuff like this because I really want to see the fantastical elements behind lots of champions explored more, as a general rule though Riot&#039;s lore department is amazing and I really appreciate that Riot lets you go above and beyond what essentially any other online game with so many characters is allowed to do from a storytelling department. Other than my desire for Beatrice to be explained more this lore drop was great and I&#039;m looking forward to more. Other than the lack of Riven, Sion, and Talon, what did everybody else think of the Noxus lore drop?
